@nunonux You could do something like this:

```C#
BsonMapper.Global.Entity<Sample>().Ctor(x => new User(x["Username"], BsonMapper.Global.Deserialize<ProfileRole>(x["ProfileRole"])));
```

The constructor mapping is only meant for simple cases (e.g. using the construtor that takes an `int` and a `string` instead of the parameterless constructor). If you need to pass complex types and enums to the constructor, it's probably best to create custom serializer and deserializer with `BsonMapper.Global.RegisterType<T>(...)`.

