@GitOffice, one way to do it would be using the `Query` method in `LiteCollection`.

```C#
var col = db.GetCollection("customers");

var query = col.Query();
var resultsPage = query.Limit(entriesPerPage).Offset((pageNumber - 1) * entriesPerPage).ToEnumerable();
```

The query will only be run when `ToEnumerable` is called, so you can call it multiple times with different limit and offset values.
If there is an index over the filter expression, the index will be used and only the desired documents will be accessed (in my example, no filter expression is present, which means the query will use the index over the `_id` field).

